  "notes": [
    "This is a virtual heartbeat monitoring protocol for testing LLM protocol reverse engineering capability",
    "Fixed length 24 bytes, all messages have the same boundary structure",
    "Uses little-endian byte order",
    "Contains node type, node ID, sequence number, uptime, load information and other fields",
    "Uses CRC32 checksum, calculated for all fields except CRC32 (first 20 bytes)",
    "Status code is automatically calculated based on CPU and memory load",
    "Suitable for distributed system health monitoring scenarios"
  ]
